Tap top-k expert indices from Qwen3-MoE forward pass.

Source data for `mtw-cache::ActivationHistogram`. When `MTW_EXPERT_LOG` is
set in the environment, every MoE forward writes one line per layer per
batch:

  [mtw-expert] layer=<L> indices=[i,j,...]\n

Indices are flattened across `[batch, seq, top_k]` — caller groups them.
When `MTW_EXPERT_LOG` is unset, the tap is a single env lookup → zero
overhead per token (cached on first call).

Apply from `mlx-swift-lm/` root:
  cd ~/Desktop/meshthatworks-deps/SwiftLM/mlx-swift-lm
  patch -p1 < ../../meshthatworks/patches/qwen3moe-expert-tap.patch

Then rebuild SwiftLM:
  cd ~/Desktop/meshthatworks-deps/SwiftLM
  swift build -c release

Run with the tap on:
  MTW_EXPERT_LOG=/tmp/mtw-experts.log mtw serve --model ...

The logs `[mtw-expert]` lines tell `mtw-cache` which experts fire on
which prompts, feeding `ActivationHistogram::record_prompt`.

--- a/Libraries/MLXLLM/Models/Qwen3MoE.swift
+++ b/Libraries/MLXLLM/Models/Qwen3MoE.swift
@@ -110,6 +110,33 @@ public class Qwen3MoEMLP: Module, UnaryLayer {
